Html:
Hey, I really love the project. The only problem I have come up against is it seems to ignore star behaviour.<br />
<br />
For example I could have the following grid<br />
<pre><code>&lt;Grid&gt;
    &lt;Grid.RowDefinitions&gt;
        &lt;RowDefinition Height=&quot;*&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;RowDefinition Height=&quot;10&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;RowDefinition Height=&quot;*&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/Grid.RowDefinitions&gt;
    &lt;TextBox HorizontalAlignment=&quot;Stretch&quot; VerticalAlignment=&quot;Stretch&quot; AcceptReturn=&quot;True&quot; HorizontalScrollBarVisibility=&quot;Auto&quot; VerticalScrollBarVisibility=&quot;Auto&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;DataGrid Grid.Row=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;/DataGrid&gt;
&lt;/Grid&gt;</code></pre>

Now usually if I was to hit return enough times the textbox's vertical scrollbar will appear, but now it starts to 'shrink' the datagrid. And vice versa, if I fill the datagrid with enough values that would usually make a scrollbar appear, it instead 'shrinks' the textbox.<br />
<br />
Do you know what would cause this and anyway to prevent it from happening?<br />
<br />
Thanks in advance<br />
<br />
<strong>EDIT</strong> Never mind, it seems to happen in WPF, when a grid is inside a scrollviewer :)<br />
